<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for odatano.dev — hosting, cookies, and GDPR rights."
>
  <article class="legal-page container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

    <p>This website is operated by Maximilian Weber (the "Operator").</p>

    <h2>Hosting</h2>
    <p>
      This website is hosted on GitHub Pages, a service provided by GitHub,
      Inc., 88 Colin P. Kelly Jr. Street, San Francisco, CA 94107, USA. When you
      visit this website, GitHub automatically collects technical access data
      including your IP address, browser type, operating system, referrer URL,
      and timestamp. This data is processed by GitHub for the purposes of
      providing the hosting service. The legal basis for this processing is Art.
      6 (1) (f) GDPR (legitimate interest in operating a functional website).
    </p>
    <p>
      GitHub's privacy practices are documented at <a
        href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-privacy-statement"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener"
        >https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-privacy-statement</a
      >.
    </p>

    <h2>Cookies, analytics, tracking</h2>
    <p>
      This website does not set any cookies and does not use any analytics,
      tracking, or advertising services.
    </p>

    <h2>External links</h2>
    <p>
      This website contains links to external websites (in particular GitHub
      repositories, Cardano explorers, NPM, and YouTube). The Operator has no
      influence over the content or privacy practices of those external sites
      and assumes no responsibility for them.
    </p>

    <h2>Your rights under GDPR</h2>
    <p>
      You have the right to information (Art. 15 GDPR), correction (Art. 16
      GDPR), deletion (Art. 17 GDPR), restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR),
      data portability (Art. 20 GDPR), and objection (Art. 21 GDPR). You also
      have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      For questions regarding data protection, please contact: info@odatano.dev
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      This privacy policy may be updated to reflect changes in the website's
      functionality or applicable law. The current version is always available
      at this URL.
    </p>

    <p class="legal-page__updated"><em>Last updated: 30.04.2026</em></p>
  </article>
</Layout>
